<div type="definition">
<p>ADULT EMPLOYED by the GOVERNMENT OR by ENTREPRENEURS to WORK FOR them.</p>
<p>[[ARBEITER]]</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general term for a corvee labourer or a conscript soldier of any kind is yì 役.</p>
<p>2. Yáo 徭 refers unambiguously to a corvee labourer and focusses prototypically on the fact that he is sent to a distant place.</p>
<p>3. Shù 戍 refers specifically to a conscript soldier sent out to guard the borders.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>勞役</p>
<p>苦工</p>
<p>徭役</p>
<p>烏拉</p>
